# Lexington Aubergine — global rules

- **Publisher:** Lexington Themes (https://lexingtonthemes.com/). Theme docs/support URLs match `README.md` (documentation, changelog for aubergine, support).
- **Package:** `@lexington/aubergine` — scoped to this repo only; do not assume other Lexington templates’ file layout.
- **Imports:** Prefer `@/` aliases (`tsconfig` maps `@/*` → `src/*`). Keep import grouping style used in existing `.astro` files (foundations/fundations, components, layouts).
- **Folder spelling:** Use `src/components/fundations/` exactly (intentional spelling, not `foundations`). Never rename it; imports and paths break.
- **UI primitives:** Reuse `src/components/fundations/` (`elements/`, `containers/`, `head/`, `icons/`, `scripts/`) and global components before adding parallel abstractions.
- **Diff discipline:** Minimal, task-focused changes. Do not widen content Zod schemas without updating every consumer (`layouts/*`, cards, pages using `entry.data`).
- **Dependencies:** Only add packages if they appear in an agreed task; do not invent features that aren’t backed by `package.json` and existing patterns.
